+## Match bucket labels & semantics (feedback #91)
+
+The match counters shown on League Summary must agree with the Matches screen segments, using the same two labels on every client:
+
+| Label | Backend source | Definition |
+|---|---|---|
+| `Mutual matches` | `/api/league/summary` → `matches_mutual`; segment via `/api/trades/matches/all` | caller's `trade_matches` rows, any status |
+| `Awaiting them` | `/api/league/summary` → `matches_awaiting`; segment via `/api/trades/awaiting` | caller's likes not yet matured into a match |
+
+The buckets are disjoint — a like leaves "Awaiting them" the moment it matures into a match. The legacy `matches_pending`/`matches_accepted` keys are deprecated (status-split; double-signaled one trade under two tiles).
+
+**Locations:** `backend/database.py` (`get_league_summary`, `load_awaiting_trades`), `web/js/app.js` (`renderLeagueSummary`), `mobile/src/screens/MatchesScreen.tsx` (segment labels). `mobile/src/screens/LeagueScreen.tsx` still renders the deprecated keys as "Pending"/"Accepted" — migration pending.
+
 ## Fairness meter semantics
 
 `fairness_score` is serialized as a float in `[0, 1]` on every trade card (consensus package-value ratio, lesser/greater). Clients render it as a percent: `Math.round(fairness * 100)` driving a 0–100% meter. Do **not** rescale server-side — both clients multiply by 100.
